ach enables new Conia-ene cyclizations with diester, ketoamide, diamide, and amide functionalities, which were previously problematic to achieve using gold catalysis as described by the Toste group. 8 This limitation of the gold-catalyzed Conia-ene cyclization was also observed in our previous work related to the synthesis of functionalized tetrahydrofurans and $\gamma$-butyrolactones.},
